Dr Thandi Ndlovu died after being in a car crash. JOHANNESBURG - Businesswoman Dr Thandi Ndlovu will be honoured with a special provincial funeral, announced acting president David Mabuza. In a statement released on Wednesday, the Presidency said Ndlovu will be honoured for her loyal service to the people of South Africa. "A Special Official Provincial Funeral Category 2 entails elements of police ceremonial honours in line with The Presidency’s State, Official and Provincial Official Funeral Policy, for distinguished persons specifically designated by the President of the Republic of South Africa', read the statement. READ: eNCA's Ben Said dies in drowning accident Ndlovu died last week Saturday in a car accident in Rustenburg, North West. Mabuza has also ordered that the national flag be flown at half-mast at all flag stations in Gauteng until the evening of the burial. Ndlovu founded Motheo Construction Group in 1997 and served as the executive chairperson.